Two illegal miners are believed to have died at Central Gold Mine in Riverlea South of Johannesburg.Police spokesman Kay Makhubele said the first miner was found on Thursday afternoon while a report of another miner being located was made on Friday. We are getting reports now that a second body has been found we are heading to the mine with authorities to verify if the body is that of a miner Makhubele said.It is believed that three miners were trapped underground after the first was found on Thursday afternoon. TMG Digital